Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of determining whether a language recognized by a deterministic finite automaton contains any pangram, which is a string that contains all the letters of the alphabet. This problem is related to formal languages and automata theory, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) sub-category. Additionally, the problem is shown to be NP-complete, which implies that the paper may also belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. The paper also analyzes various other language classes and problems around pangrams, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), or cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-categories.
